caption: I just moved to Chicago & have been dying to try Nandos. I finally did & I was skeptical at first BUT I was amazed. I ate it twice in a day because it was just that good. The chicken & flamed grilled corn are 10/10 pineapple lemonade slaps & the gelato was perfection.
Chicken is juicy, with in door dining everyone was socially distanced and just a great feeling at the restaurant
The service wasn’t to bad, neither was the food. Just wasn’t my kind of restaurant, it’s worth at least a try. Won’t know if you like it til you try it.
It definitely hit the spot ! Love these wings ! Thanks Guys!
Nando's never disappoints.  Food is awesome customer service is over the top!

I love this place beyond words! The staff is always so delightful and patient with my inability to make a decision on menu items. They're quick to suggest dishes based off what you've liked in the past and the food is always prepared perfectly.

My experience at this place was absolutely not great. The staff working there was very rude. This happened on 29 January 2021. We were visiting Chicago. My wife and I wanted to Nando’s she tried it before and this was my first time at Nando’s and may be my last time. The restaurant has good ambiance so after we were done eating we wanted to take couple of pictures and requested the staff to click one, they did but we didn’t liked it so we were taking pictures and then an African American female asks us to stop and leave. It was quite rude. I gave one star just for food. Thanks for creating a bad memory in our vacation. Respecting your customers is equally important. If we don’t matter you business owner’s wont matter to us soon.

Consistently poor experiences coming here. This is the dirtiest location I’ve been to for Nando’s. The customer service is next to awful. They’ve refused to provide glasses of water many times. They have also messed up more order more than once. You can find yourself waiting a long time for your order.  The food is sometimes pretty good though.
The chicken was not fully cooked and my husband ended up Ill.  We will never be back as this was the 2nd bad experience in a row 😳

It ruined my meal as I ordered the hot sauce chicken and that would have been the balance. Young woman “working” at the front counter was sitting on a bar stool, didn’t even bother saying hello or any niceties. Then SHE asked US if we had already paid for our food. Shouldn’t they know that? Then she said “feel free to leave a tip”. What?! Who says that?? Hire some better people.

I had never eaten here before tonight.  This company graciously provided free meals to Healthcare workers and that is why I tried it.  It was a 1/4 chicken that was mainly breast meat. It was absolutely delicious!!!  The meat was super moist with a smokey taste and the spices were perfect. I got hot flavor and it was perfect heat and flavor, not scorching.  I would pay for this any day but am beyond grateful for the complimentary meal. Support this restaurant that is supporting healthcare and producing a fabulous product. Thank you Nando's.
